    • Method Detail

      • scanInfinitely

        public final ScanOptions scanInfinitely()
        Scan indefinitely until BleManager.stopScan() is called. If this is called after scanPeriodically(Interval, Interval), this will override the periodic scan.

      • scanFor

        public final ScanOptions scanFor(Interval time)
        Scan for the specified amount of time. This method implies a one-time scan. If you want to perform a periodic scan, then use scanPeriodically(Interval, Interval) instead. If this is called after scanPeriodically(Interval, Interval), it will override the periodic scan.

      • forceIndefinite

        public final ScanOptions forceIndefinite(boolean force)
        Force a indefinite scan. If you choose to scan indefinitely, and don't set this, SweetBlue will automatically pause the scan, and resume it shortly thereafter, to make sure scan results keep coming in as expected. If you pass in true here, the scan will just run until you call BleManager.stopScan(), or BleManager.stopAllScanning(). There's really no reason to do this, but it's left in here to be flexible.

      • scanPeriodically

        public final ScanOptions scanPeriodically(Interval scanTime,
                                          Interval pauseTime)
        Do a periodic scan. If you want to do a one-time scan, then use scanFor(Interval) instead.

      • withScanFilter

        public final ScanOptions withScanFilter(BleManagerConfig.ScanFilter filter)
        Set a BleManagerConfig.ScanFilter for this scan.

      • withDiscoveryListener

        public final ScanOptions withDiscoveryListener(BleManager.DiscoveryListener listener)
        Set a BleManager.DiscoveryListener for this scan.

      • asHighPriority

        public final ScanOptions asHighPriority(boolean highPriority)
        This will set the scan to be of the highest priority. This should ONLY be used if you absolutely need it! With this active, ONLY scanning will happen (even if you call connect on a device, or read/write, etc), until you call BleManager.stopScan() or BleManager.stopPeriodicScan(), or BleManager.stopAllScanning().
